This paper is about active learning for machine learning, specifically for linear regression problems. The paper proposes a novel approach that considers informativeness, representativeness, and diversity. These are all topics that fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses datasets from various application domains, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV), data structures (cs.DS), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
